get user id from string "MAY 2013" WordPress Codex "Function Reference"
=======================================================================

NAME
----

get user id from string - Get a numeric user ID from either an email address or a login. If a

SYNOPSIS
--------

Get a numeric user ID from either an email address or a login. If a
number is sent to the function, that number is returned as the id.

USAGE
-----

` <?php get_user_id_from_string( $string ); ?> `

PARAMETERS
----------

 `$string` 
:   ([*string*](/How_to_Pass_Tag_Parameters#String "How to Pass Tag Parameters"))
    (*required*) String representation of the user to lookup the ID for.
    May be either the user's login (their username), or the email
    address registered in WordPress. A numeric string is considered to
    be an existing user ID and is simply returned as such.
    Default: *None*

RETURN VALUES
-------------

 `` `(int)`{style="color:gray"} 
:   ID of the user specified by \$string on success, null if no user is
    found.

SOURCE FILE
-----------

`get_user_id_from_string()` is located in `wp-includes/ms-functions.php`

CHANGE LOG
----------

-   Since @WPMU
-   Deprecated [3.6.0](/Version_3.6 "Version 3.6")

